{"_record_type": "fragment", "type": "expert_knowledge", "content": "# Q: fix: MCP servers with OAuth lose authentication when access token expires mid-session\n**Source:** https://github.com/google-gemini/gemini-cli/issues/23776\n\n## The Problem / Request\n## Bug Description\n\nMCP servers that require OAuth authentication lose their auth after the access token expires (typically 1 hour). Once expired, all subsequent MCP tool calls fail and there is no recovery mechanism \u2014 the only workaround is restarting the CLI.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThe OAuth access token is baked into the HTTP transport headers **once at connection time** (in `createTransport()`) and **never refreshed** during the session lifetime. The `getValidToken()` method in `MCPOAuthProvider` has proper token refresh logic using the refresh token, but it is only called during initial connection setup.\n\nWhen the token expires:\n1. The transport continues sending the expired token\n2. The server returns 401\n3. `McpCallableTool.callTool()` catches it as a generic error\n4. The error is returned to the model as `{ isError: true }`\n5. No token refresh, no reconnection, no transport recreation\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. Configure an MCP server that requires OAuth authentication (e.g., one that issues tokens with a 1-hour TTL)\n2. Start gemini-cli and authenticate with the MCP server\n3. Use tools from the MCP server successfully\n4. Wait for the access token to expire (or set a short TTL on the OAuth provider)\n5. Try to use an MCP tool again\n\n**Expected:** The CLI refreshes the token automatically and the tool call succeeds\n**Actual:** The tool call fails with a 401 error, and all subsequent calls continue to fail\n\n## Additional Context\n\n- Restarting the CLI fixes the issue because `Config.initialize()` creates fresh MCP connections, and `createTransport()` calls `getValidToken()` which refreshes the expired token using the stored refresh token.\n- When resuming a conversation after restart, the old \"MCP failed\" errors appear in history but don't affect the new connections.\n- Related: #798, #844", "timestamp": null, "embedding": [0.5644604563713074, 0.9936212301254272, -3.44852352142334, -1.2890446186065674, 1.7871217727661133, -0.8721809387207031, 0.2766599953174591, 0.6029902696609497, 1.2445534467697144, -1.0487985610961914, -0.9795278906822205, 1.8269810676574707, -0.4418419897556305, -0.7679727077484131, 0.8209298253059387, -0.4832645058631897, 1.0391956567764282, -0.7335895299911499, -0.7492241263389587, 0.1924670934677124, 0.23556436598300934, -1.2198065519332886, -0.22185079753398895, -0.5375921130180359, 1.1958783864974976, 0.532437264919281, 0.5702528357505798, 1.3619396686553955, -1.042434811592102, 0.09598708897829056, 1.9115898609161377, -1.2124993801116943, 0.3088221251964569, -0.06685550510883331, -0.5927309393882751, -0.2579984664916992, 0.1500377357006073, 0.3686162829399109, -0.10184819251298904, -0.37257683277130127, 1.2964086532592773, 0.5166792273521423, 1.047742486000061, 0.6171581149101257, 0.19102732837200165, -0.1767355352640152, 1.243127703666687, 0.6072240471839905, 1.0772956609725952, -1.3763232231140137, 0.36984601616859436, -0.21656815707683563, -0.5111438035964966, 0.29989007115364075, 0.46806037425994873, 0.7090347409248352, 0.21395833790302277, 0.349450021982193, -0.31587332487106323, -0.4914361238479614, 1.4945085048675537, 1.0104153156280518, -0.07812562584877014, 1.6022815704345703, 0.41578760743141174, -0.6678123474121094, 0.061195630580186844, 0.397270143032074, 1.0776561498641968, -0.3230268657207489, 0.46896466612815857, -0.10508838295936584, -0.04282244294881821, 0.7803307771682739, -0.25341513752937317, 0.5395918488502502, -0.6112931370735168, -1.1940226554870605, 0.14175130426883698, -0.11800455302000046, -0.45449915528297424, 0.1637832522392273, 0.9851080179214478, 0.5463483333587646, 0.663519024848938, 0.026899389922618866, -0.7082951664924622, -0.35268357396125793, -0.6206130385398865, 1.741894960403442