{"_record_type": "fragment", "type": "expert_knowledge", "content": "he expired token using the stored refresh token.\n- When resuming a conversation after restart, the old \"MCP failed\" errors appear in history but don't affect the new connections.\n- Related: #798, #844\n\n## Environment\n\n- OS: macOS\n- Node.js: v20+\n- gemini-cli: latest main\n\n## Proposed Fix\n\nAdd automatic reconnection with token refresh when MCP auth errors are detected:\n\n1. **`McpClient.connect()` onerror handler**: Detect auth errors and trigger auto-reconnect instead of permanently marking as DISCONNECTED\n2. **New `McpClient.reconnectOnAuthError()` method**: Disconnects, reconnects (token refresh happens automatically via `getValidToken()`), and rediscovers tools. Concurrent calls are coalesced.\n3. **`McpCallableTool.callTool()`**: Detect 401 errors and notify the MCP client to reconnect. The error is still returned to the model so it can retry on the next turn.\n4. **`discoverTools()`**: Thread the auth error callback through to `McpCallableTool`\n\nI have a working implementation and will submit a PR shortly.\n\n## The Solution / Discussion\n### Response 1\nFound possible duplicate issues:\n\n- #23296\n- #18895\n\nIf you believe this is not a duplicate, please remove the `status/possible-duplicate` label.\n<!-- gemini-cli-deduplication -->\n\n", "timestamp": null, "embedding": [0.397970050573349, 0.1547815054655075, -2.94705867767334, -1.4525387287139893, 1.0409157276153564, -0.9840809106826782, 0.4376881718635559, -0.4381554126739502, 1.5915324687957764, -0.7539010047912598, -1.5831990242004395, 1.8452262878417969, -0.20617644488811493, -0.1336105763912201, 0.5401003956794739, -0.9541341066360474, 1.095550775527954, -0.6311944127082825, -0.4732767343521118, -0.055165454745292664, 0.4122818112373352, -1.0272905826568604, -0.18798235058784485, -0.33401697874069214, 1.3443490266799927, 0.9831317663192749, 0.27215203642845154, 1.4416180849075317, -1.3342511653900146, -0.07128083705